  "metadata": {
    "type": "targeted_grid",
    "name": "switching_ideology_threshold",
    "description": "Validates that ideology_strength correctly scales the effective switching threshold for non-neutral economic nodes.\nWith econ_neutral_fraction=0.0 all economic nodes carry their ideology, so only ideology_strength determines whether the actual price gap triggers a switch.\nActual price gap measured from previous runs: ~14.3% (not 19% as originally assumed). The original spec used econ_switching_threshold=0.14 and econ_inertia=0.17, which put the threshold at exactly the gap edge and added probabilistic blocking \u2014 resulting in zero switches across all scenarios.\nFix: econ_switching_threshold=0.10, econ_inertia=0.05. Effective threshold formula:\n  effective_threshold = econ_switching_threshold * (1 + ideology_strength * 2.0)\n\nAt the actual ~14.3% price gap (with threshold=0.10):\n  ideology_strength=0.00 \u2192 effective_threshold=10.0% \u2192 SWITCHES (gap >> threshold)\n  ideology_strength=0.15 \u2192 effective_threshold=13.0% \u2192 SWITCHES (gap > threshold)\n  ideology_strength=0.25 \u2192 effective_threshold=15.0% \u2192 WON'T switch (gap < threshold)\n  ideology_strength=0.40 \u2192 effective_threshold=18.0% \u2192 definitely WON'T switch\n\nThis brackets the switchover at ideology \u2248 0.21 (where effective_threshold = 14.3%).\nExpected gradient:\n  ideology=0.00 \u2192 v27_econ_share drifts toward 100% (all nodes follow winner)\n  ideology=0.15 \u2192 v27_econ_share drifts (just below cutoff)\n  ideology=0.25 \u2192 v27_econ_share flat (just above cutoff)\n  ideology=0.40 \u2192 v27_econ_share flat (clearly ideological)\n\nWith inertia=0.05 (5% probabilistic block) the gradient should be clean and consistent across replicates.\nRun with:\n  python 3_run_sweep.py \\\n    --input switching_ideology_threshold/build_manifest.json \\\n    --namespace sweep-ideology-thresh \\\n    --results-dir switching_ideology_threshold/results \\\n    --duration 4000 --retarget-interval 144 --interval 2 \\\n    --use-sigmoid\n\nNamespace to create first:\n  kubectl create namespace sweep-ideology-thresh\n",
    "spec_file": "specs/switching_ideology_threshold.yaml",
